## Phase 5: CLI — User Management Commands

All commands connect directly to the control plane DB (same pattern as existing CLI commands).

### `lumiverb create-user`

```
lumiverb create-user --email EMAIL [--role admin|editor|viewer]
```

- Prompts for password (hidden, confirmed twice)
- Validates: email format, password minimum 12 characters
- Hashes with bcrypt (cost factor 12)
- Inserts into `users` with a generated UUID
- Enforces last-admin invariant: if role would demote/skip the only admin path, warn and abort
- Default role: `viewer` (caller must explicitly pass `--role admin` for the bootstrap case)

```bash
lumiverb create-user --email admin@example.com --role admin
# → Password: ••••••••••••
# → Confirm:  ••••••••••••
# → User created: admin@example.com (admin)

lumiverb create-user --email admin@example.com --role admin
# → Error: email already registered
```

### `lumiverb list-users`

```
lumiverb list-users
```

Prints a table of all users: email, role, last login.

```
EMAIL                    ROLE     LAST LOGIN
admin@example.com        admin    2026-03-20 14:32
editor@example.com       editor   2026-03-18 09:11
viewer@example.com       viewer   never
```

### `lumiverb set-user-role`

```
lumiverb set-user-role --email EMAIL --role admin|editor|viewer
```

Updates the user's role. Enforces the last-admin invariant.

```bash
lumiverb set-user-role --email editor@example.com --role admin
# → Role updated: editor@example.com → admin
```

### `lumiverb remove-user`

```
lumiverb remove-user --email EMAIL
```

Prompts for confirmation before deleting. Enforces the last-admin invariant.

```bash
lumiverb remove-user --email viewer@example.com
# → Remove viewer@example.com? [y/N]: y
# → User removed.

lumiverb remove-user --email admin@example.com
# → Error: cannot remove the last admin
```

