## Required Tests

### Schema (`@pytest.mark.migration`)
- `users` table created with correct columns and constraints
- `password_reset_tokens` table created with correct columns
- `api_keys.role` column added with default `"admin"`; existing rows unaffected

### Auth endpoints (`@pytest.mark.slow`)
- `POST /v1/auth/login` with valid credentials → 200 with JWT containing correct role
- `POST /v1/auth/login` with wrong password → 401
- `POST /v1/auth/login` with unknown email → 401, response time comparable to wrong password
- `POST /v1/auth/forgot-password` with unknown email → 204 (no enumeration)
- `POST /v1/auth/reset-password` with valid token → 204, password updated
- `POST /v1/auth/reset-password` with expired token → 400
- `POST /v1/auth/reset-password` with already-used token → 400

### Middleware (`@pytest.mark.slow`)
- Request with valid Admin JWT → resolves tenant, `role == "admin"`
- Request with valid Viewer JWT → resolves tenant, `role == "viewer"`
- Request with expired JWT → 401
- Request with tampered JWT → 401
- Request with valid API key (not a JWT) → resolves via API key path, `role == "admin"`
- Both token types coexist in the same running server

### Role enforcement (`@pytest.mark.slow`)
- Admin JWT → can call `POST /v1/libraries` (editor-gated write route) ✓
- Editor JWT → can call `POST /v1/libraries` ✓
- Viewer JWT → `POST /v1/libraries` → 403
- Admin JWT → can call `GET /v1/users` ✓
- Editor JWT → `GET /v1/users` → 403
- Viewer JWT → `GET /v1/users` → 403

### User management API (`@pytest.mark.slow`)
- `POST /v1/users` → 201, user created
- `POST /v1/users` with duplicate email → 409
- `PATCH /v1/users/{id}` role change → 200, role updated
- `PATCH /v1/users/{id}` demoting last Admin → 409 `last_admin`
- `DELETE /v1/users/{id}` → 204, user removed
- `DELETE /v1/users/{id}` removing last Admin → 409 `last_admin`
- `DELETE /v1/users/{id}` where `user_id == caller` → 400

### CLI (`@pytest.mark.slow`)
- `create-user` with new email → user row inserted with correct role and password hash
- `create-user` with duplicate email → error, no duplicate row
- `set-user-role` on last Admin → error, no change
- `remove-user` on last Admin → error, no deletion
- `list-users` → prints all users for the tenant
